 Hi, I am making an FPS game, and for it I have hid the mouse icon, and made an image label as a custom, resizable cross hare, so that I can change its size when a player does ADS. 
Currently, when a player holds the right mouse button, my script lerps the cframe of the guns viewmodel to the ADS position, so it creates a smooth movement between ADS and normal. I have tried to do tweening to make it so that the cross hair will contract when a player holds down the right mouse button, then expand when they release it, however its really buggy. Right now if i make the tween go any slower than 0.1 seconds, the cross hair just disappears when the player holds down rmb, then reappears when the tween is finished, and the same happens when rmb is released. At 0.1 seconds, the tween is non-existent - the size just changes, with pretty much no actual “contraction” movement like a tween should be - it basically looks as if i just ran gui.Size = Udim2.new(newsize) rather than did gui:TweenSize(). So, obviously gui doesnt have a CFrame feature for learping, however is there something equivalent or similar I can do to make the crosshair UI expand and contract smoothly, similar to how the gun viewmodel moves smoothly between the ADS and normal position when RMB is pressed/released? 
